```julia
function add_yearmonth(df)
    df[:ym] = Dates.format.(df[:dt], "Y/m");
end
```
In this code, the `add_yearmonth` function takes a DataFrame `df` as input. It creates a new column `ym` by using the `Dates.format` function to convert each DateTime value in the `dt` column into a string in the format "Y/m". The resulting strings are then assigned to the `ym` column of the DataFrame.
